      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Today is the \"Long Night of Research\" in Linz, Austria. 35 exhibitors at 18 locations, including universities, colleges, research institutions, companies, hospitals and museums open their doors to everyone and show for one evening what usually takes place in closed laboratories.\nOur Institute of Integrated Circuits at the Johannes Kepler University in Linz also shows some awesome stuff:\n- wafer.space chip under a digital microscope\n- Snake on TinyTapeout 06\n- Arcade Machine showing the layout of a 12-Bit SAR ADC\n- poster with recent open-source chips\n- 3D printed inverter\n- wafers, silicon ingots, etc. \nOf course, the TinyTapeout hat must not be missing. \uD83D\uDE09\nIt is a blast to see the interest in chips from young to old. \uD83D\uDE4C",
      "author": {
